OL,3,CRobert Rhodes jailed for life for
OL,4,Cwife's murder after re-trial
OL,6,FWarning: This report contains details
OL,7,Fsome people may find distressing
OL,9,FRobert Rhodes has been sentenced to
OL,10,Flife with a minimum of 29 years and
OL,11,Fsix months in prison for the "wicked"
OL,12,Fmurder of his estranged wife, Dawn
OL,13,FRhodes, in 2016, after new evidence
OL,14,Fprovided by their child prompted a re-
OL,15,Ftrial.
OL,17,FRhodes was convicted in December after
OL,18,Fthe jury returned a unanimous verdict,
OL,19,Ffollowing an eight-week re-trial at
OL,20,Fthe Inner Crown Court in London, in a
OL,21,Frare double jeopardy case.
