OL,4,Cwife's murder after re-trial
OL,6,FThe judge listed factors that
OL,7,Fcontributed to the sentence,
OL,8,Fincluding: "significant premeditation
OL,9,Fand planning", "grotesque involvement
OL,10,Fof (the child)", "infliction of
OL,11,Fphysical injury on (the child)", the
OL,12,Fcontents of the 999 call on the night,
OL,13,Fthe domestic nature of the crime,
OL,14,FRhodes' use of cocaine ahead of the
OL,15,Fmurder, the "great distress and
OL,16,Fanxiety" which Dawn Rhodes had
OL,17,Fexperienced before her death, and
OL,18,F"emotional manipulation" of Dawn
OL,19,FRhodes before her murder.
