OL,6,FMrs Justice Ellenbogen described the
OL,7,Fchild's decision to reveal the
OL,8,Finformation as "courageous". During
OL,9,Fthe sentencing remarks, the child was
OL,10,Freferred to as "X" to protect their
OL,11,Fidentity.
OL,13,F"For the rest of X's life, X will have
OL,14,Fto live with X's involvement in Dawn's
OL,15,Fdeath," the judge said, adding that
OL,16,Fthe events would have a "substantial
OL,17,Fand enduring impact" on the child's
OL,18,Flife.
