OL,3,CRobert Rhodes jailed for life for
OL,4,Cwife's murder after re-trial
OL,6,FThe child had been a key witness
OL,7,Fduring the trial when Rhodes was
OL,8,Facquitted and had been under ten years
OL,9,Fold at the time of the murder in June
OL,10,F2016.
OL,12,FIn the re-trial, jurors heard about
OL,13,FRhodes' plot to "get rid of mummy", as
OL,14,Fwell as the effort he made to keep the
OL,15,Ftruth concealed.
OL,17,FRhodes refused to attend court for his
OL,18,Fsentencing, despite being fit to do so.
